properties.text: Welcome to the [b]3D shape interactive tour![/b] 3D shapes are an easy way to add a 3D appearance to your games. Use the arrow keys to control the player. Notice how the 3D shapes look as the player moves around. [b]Run to the right[/b] to see more examples.
The [b]Z height[/b] of a 3D shape can be adjusted. The camera is at a Z height of 100 and looks down. So a shape with a height of 50 extends half way to the camera.

The [b]Z elevation[/b] of a 3D shape can also be adjusted to move the shape up and down on the Z axis. This can be used to do things like place shapes on top of one another. Sprites and some other objects can also be moved up and down with Z elevation.
As well as boxes, the 3D shape object can be set to a variety of different [b]shapes[/b].
All these features can be combined to assemble basic 3D level designs.
Collisions for 3D shapes still work in 2D like normal sprites. If you want to run under a 3D shape, remove or disable the Solid behavior.

[outline=white][size=48]The end![/size]
We hope you enjoy using this feature![/outline]
Additional appearances can be created by hiding individual faces of each kind of shape.
